the heartache and stress caused to both of us is hard to adequately describe. &#10;She finally got help at the age of 13 after years in which (as I now know) some teachers actually colluded with the bullying. Twenty years later we finally achieved a good mother daughter relationship and she has at last gained what she has always been capable of - a professional qualification. &#10;Now of course not every child is bullied but no child deserves it. Schools should be protecting our children from this behaviour sadly they often still don't. &#10;To blithely assume that all but a small number of kids are safer in school than they are at home is an insult to the vast majority of decent caring parents. I do not make the opposite conclusion but in the majority of cases a child is safer at home because the child adult ratio is more favourable than it is at school. &#10;As others have said home education can result in faster learning (one to one tuition always does it inevutably addresses individual problems better than a teacher with 30 pupils can. &#10;Home education could have saved my daughter and I over 20 years of unhappiness. we are not alone and we are amongst the lucky ones. Sadly some parents can today only visit their child's grave. &#10;I urge all parents who cannot persuade the school that bullying is occuring to consider home education. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1638" language="en" documentId="926" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="annetan42" date="06 November 2009 4:22pm" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://discussion.theguardian.com/comment-permalink/6745592" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="14" thumbsDown="0" origId="926" notes="" title="Ridiculous rules for home schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="11"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="12" end="176"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="177" end="377"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="378" end="674"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="55" sofa="1" begin="675" end="834"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="59" sofa="1" begin="835" end="1155"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="63" sofa="1" begin="1156" end="1339"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="67" sofa="1" begin="1340" end="1533"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="71" sofa="1" begin="1534" end="1638"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51 55 59 63 67 71"/></xmi:XMI>